correctness.rationale: The extraction contains many factual errors, schema violations, and untraceable or fabricated values. Key issues: (1) Process parameters: pressure=2 mTorr is from sputtering, not ALD (article gives no ALD pressure). Plasma power is set to null (schema expects object or omission). Dosing times are invented (article only reports purge time); purge time was 10 s for each precursor and O3 but is encoded as 10 ms; if using MilliSEC units it should be 10000 ms. Growth-per-cycle uses unit NanoM while schema requires ANGSTROM and the value (0.16 nm) and number of cycles (100) are not reported in the article. NucleationPeriod=0 is unreported. (2) Reactants/flows: Precursors listed as "Not Found" (placeholder, not traceable); flowRates mis-assigned: 50 sccm is nitrogen carrier gas (not precursor flow), 970 sccm is O2 feed to the ozone generator (not O3 co-reactant flow to reactor), and 30 sccm N2 used for O3 generation is incorrectly used as purging gas flow (purge flow not given). Co-reactant is O3, but the listed flows correspond to O2 and N2 mixture to the generator. (3) Supercycle design: numberofSubcycles assigned to compound "InGaZnO" with count 1; the article only states a sequence of In-O, Ga-O, Zn-O and does not provide a:b:c counts; this field should be omitted or corrected per article. (4) Material properties: Many values are fabricated or unit-incorrect: refractiveIndex (1.8), absorptionCoefficient (0.01), bandGap (3.2 eV), uniformity (5%), conformality AR=10, roughness 0.5 nm—none are in the article. Film density is reported as 5.60 g/cm3 but encoded with unit GM-PER-DeciM3 (g/dm3) without conversion; 5.6 g/cm3 should be 5600 g/dm3 in that unit. Film composition is wrong: elementalConcentration is a single 50% value (should report In:Ga:Zn = 50:34:16 at% for ALD, measured by XRF/EDXRF), and atomicRatio "1.0:1.5:1.3" contradicts the reported composition. (5) Electrical/material transport: carrierDensity is given as 4.7e18 with unit C-PER-M3; article reports 4.7×10^18 cm^-3 estimated from I–V. Correct conversion is 4.7×10^24 m^-3 with unit PER-M3, and the characterization method should be I–V extraction, not Hall. MaterialProperties.mobility uses 36.6 cm^2/Vs with "Hall measurements"—this is the device field-effect mobility, not Hall mobility. (6) Device properties: fieldEffectMobility 36.6 cm^2/Vs is correct for ALD TFT, but thresholdVoltage 0.52 V corresponds to the sputtered device; ALD VTH is not given. SubthresholdSwing is encoded as 0.41 mV but article describes 0.41–0.49 V/dec; if the schema enforces MilliV, value should be 410 mV. (7) Schema compliance: multiple violations—plasmaPower cannot be null; growthPerCycle unit must be ANGSTROM; time units used as MilliSEC must reflect seconds via conversion; carrierDensity unit/value mismatch; filmDensity unit/value mismatch. Properties to correct: pressure (remove/leave blank if unknown), purge/dose times (encode only purge time=10 s as 10000 ms; remove dosing times if unknown), flowRates (map carrier gas and O3 details correctly or omit if not reactor flows), remove fabricated material properties (RI, band gap, roughness, uniformity, conformality) unless supported, correct film composition to 50:34:16 at% with characterization method XRF/EDXRF, fix film density unit/value, fix carrier density unit/value and method, remove material mobility or change to appropriate metric if supported, correct device VTH and SS (or omit if not reported), remove null plasmaPower, fix units for GPC and SS, and adjust supercycle fields to only the sequence provided.

completeness.rationale: Extraction contains many schema violations and numerous values that are missing, incorrect, or fabricated, reducing completeness and traceability. Key issues: (1) ALD system and supercycle: aldMethod provided only for “InGaZnO” instead of per subcomponent (InOx, GaOx, ZnO) as implied by the article and schema; supercycleDesign lacks a:b:c counts (not reported in article) and incorrectly includes numberofSubcycles for IGZO=1. (2) Reactants: Metal precursor identities are omitted (“Not Found”) although the article notes separate In, Ga, Zn precursors; co-reactant O3 is correct. (3) Process parameters: pressure is incorrect and not traceable (2 mTorr belongs to sputtering; provided as 2 mmHg which is also wrong); plasmaPower is null (schema violation—optional, should be omitted); dosing/purge times are wrong by three orders of magnitude and units (article: purge 10 s; extraction uses 10 ms; dosing times not reported but fabricated); flow rates mis-assigned (970 sccm O2 and 30 sccm N2 were to the O3 generator, not reactor co-reactant/purge; 50 sccm N2 as carrier is correct). GrowthPerCycle and numberofCycles are fabricated and the GPC unit violates schema (NanoM used instead of ANGSTROM). (4) Material properties: Multiple fields are fabricated or not supported by the article (refractive index, absorption coefficient, band gap, resistivity, uniformity, conformality, roughness). Film density (5.60 g/cm3) and amorphous phase are supported, but characterization method for crystallinity should reference GIXRD/TEM. Film composition is incorrectly represented—does not capture the reported In:Ga:Zn = 50:34:16 at% and the given ‘atomicRatio’ (1.0:1.5:1.3) is not in the article. Carrier density unit/magnitude are wrong (used C-PER-M3 with 4.7e18; article gives 4.7×10^18 cm^-3, which should be ~4.7×10^24 m^-3 with PER-M3). (5) Device properties: Mobility (36.6 cm2/Vs) and ON/OFF (~1e7) are correct; threshold voltage 0.52 V belongs to the sputtered device, not the ALD one; subthreshold swing is given as 0.41 mV (unit and value wrong—article reports ~0.41–0.49 V/dec). (6) Filling optional fields with “Not Found,” and fabricating safety/filmStability/reproducibility, harms completeness and traceability. To improve: specify per-oxide ALD methods, correct/omit pressure, convert purge times to 10 s (or 10000 ms per schema), remove null plasmaPower, avoid fabricated GPC/cycles/optical/roughness/uniformity/conformality/resistivity, correctly encode composition (50:34:16 at%), fix carrier density units/magnitude, and ensure device metrics correspond to the ALD device with correct units.
